flowRoot.flowPara: Shown when the device is woken up and is locked. Switches to the authentication state with a click, tap or key press.
Authentication is shown on key press or click. This state is also shown by default if a user is selected from the user selection screen.
Session selection menu, OS logo.
∙ A summary of notifications that have been "shown" while the device has been locked.
∙ Media controls for music/video, when it's playing.
∙ Smart card icon when smart card authentication is available.
∙ Fingerprint icon when fingerprint authentication is available.
∙ A back button, which navigates to the user selection screen.
Esc returns to the presentation state, if that was previously shown.
Includes:

Messages that are required to be shown on login. This approach of showing it as a modal overlay might not pass muster but every other solution is horribly awkward. Return or Esc would dismiss it, at least...

When notifications arrive and the screen is locked, they are shown in white on black. This behavior should be configurable, and probably off by default. We probably need to think about variants in which notification content is shown, too.
Too fast! Please swipe again on the fingerprint reader

Incorrect password message. There shouldn't be any delay between an incorrect attempt and being able to retry. However, after three attempts input should be insensitive for 5 seconds and the message should read "Three incorrect attempts. Please wait to try again."

Clock and user picture are centered 38.2% from the top of the screen. Fingerprint and smartcard icons have their vertical center at 23.6% of the screen height. Other elements are positioned in relation to these.
If fingerprint/smartcard icons aren't present, the user name occupies their space.
OS logo is positioned in relation to the screen edge, in absolute units.
